https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/7KFyISCQVKwlX6myW7vbTnsF9wo.jpg 120 metres down off the wild coast of South Africa lives an animal once thought to have been extinct for 65 million years - the coelacanth, locally known as Gombessa. A dinosaur fish, a living fossil, that remains the only link connecting fish to terrestrial tetrapods: its fins contain the beginning of reptile and mammal leg bones!
